{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"aba4c59c369d45698","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Use WebSearch and WebFetch to research the ARCHITECTURE of Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve (2025). I need specific, cited facts with exact source URLs.\n\nFocus on:\n- The evolutionary coding pipeline: ensemble of Gemini LLMs (Gemini Flash + Gemini Pro) that mutate/edit code\n- How the evolutionary loop works: population of programs, prompt sampler, LLM ensemble generating code via diffs/edits, automated evaluators scoring candidates, program database / selection\n- Why an ensemble (Flash for breadth/throughput, Pro for depth/quality)\n- That it edits whole codebases / functions, uses diff-based edits\n\nPrefer primary sources: deepmind.google blog post (search \"AlphaEvolve a Gemini-powered coding agent deepmind\"), the arxiv white paper / DeepMind white paper PDF.\n\nReturn a list of falsifiable, specific claims. Each claim MUST have its exact source URL. Quote DeepMind's wording where possible. Do not write files — return findings as your final text message."},"uuid":"6e31e71d-bd7c-498f-8950-cf552f14d2f1","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:28.558Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
